    Package Description
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.binding.model
    Provides the core implementation of the Metaschema model (gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common) represented as Java class annotations (gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.binding.model.annotations).

    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model
    Support for loading Metaschema information from an XML-based Metaschema model.
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common
    Provides interfaces, abstract implementation classes, and excptions that are used in Metaschema APIs.
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common.definition
    Representations of Metaschema model definitions.
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common.instance
    Representations of Metaschema model instances used in a Metaschema assembly or field.
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common.metapath
    Support for working with Metapath expressions.
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common.metapath.evaluate.instance
    Support for evaluating a Metapath expression against Metaschema definitions.
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common.metapath.format
    Support for defining and evaluating Metapath functions.
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common.metapath.item
    The Metapath type system, which overlays the Metaschema type system defined in gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common.datatype.adapter.
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common.util
    Various utilities and helper methods.
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.definitions  
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.instances  
    gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.xml
    An implementation of the Metaschema model (gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common) using an underlying XML format.
  • Classes in gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common.definition used by gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.binding.model 
    Class Description
    IAssemblyDefinition  
    IDefinition  
    IFieldDefinition  
    IFlagDefinition  
    IFlaggedDefinition
    This marker interface represents a definition that consists of flags, and potentially a simple value (for a field) or complex model contents (for an assembly).
    IModelContainer
    Indicates that the Metaschema definition type has a complex model that can contain flags, field, and assembly instances.
    INamedDefinition
    This marker interface is used for some collections that contain various named definitions.
    INamedModelDefinition
    This marker interface identifies a definition that is intended to be part of an Assembly's model.
    INamedValuedDefinition
    This marker interface is used for some collections that contain various named definitions that have an associated value.
    IValuedDefinition
    This marker interface identifies Metaschema definition types that have associated values (i.e., field, flag).
